So, when it's just the foundress (and/or her lazy sister co-foundresses) they're extremely docile because if they die, the whole nest die, so you can get all up in their grill and they won't do anything.

If you hand feed them, then they and all of their daughters will not see you as a threat and either completely ignore you or hold on to the edge of the nest with their back legs and reach way out to get fed delicious honey.

I read some actual scholarly published papers that say they can probably recognize specific humans because they have super good visual acuity and can recognize individual members of their own nest.

This is species-dependent, so like, look up what kind of paper wasps they are before you decide to tongue-feed them.
